HEADWORD: Trichiasis
<hw>Tri*chi"a*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/, fr. <grk>tri`x</grk>, <grk>tricho`s</grk>, hair.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A disease of the eye, in which the eyelashes,
being turned in upon the eyeball, produce constant irritation by the
motion of the lids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trichina</ent>⟦br⟧
